    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ST. GEORGE, UTAH \u2013\nFresno State erased multiple deficits and briefly grabbed the lead in the 10th inning, but Utah Tech answered with a walk-off two-run home run to hand the Bulldogs an 8-7 loss on Thursday night at Bruce Hurst Field.\nThe Bulldogs dropped to 7-14 on the season despite totaling 12 hits, including home runs from\nMarcus Nolen\nand\nZach Plasschaert\n. Utah Tech improved to 15-8 with the extra-inning win.\nBrady Hewitt\npaced Fresno State with two hits and a run scored, while\nOwen Faust\nadded two hits.\u00a0Nolen\u00a0finished with two\u00a0RBIs\u00a0on his fourth-inning homer,\nEthan Payne\ndrove in two with a key single in the eighth, and\nRyan De La Maza\ndelivered a pinch-hit RBI single during the Bulldogs' late rally.\u00a0Plasschaert's\u00a0solo homer in the top of the 10th gave Fresno State a 7-6 edge before Utah Tech responded in the bottom half.\nHow it happened\nFresno State struck first in the opening inning when Hewitt doubled and came home on\nMikey Boyd's\nRBI single through the right side. Utah Tech answered in the bottom of the first, then took control in the third with three runs, helped by a throwing error and a sacrifice fly, to move in front 4-1.\nThe Bulldogs chipped away in the fourth when\nCayden Munster\ndoubled and\u00a0Nolen\u00a0launched a two-run homer to left center, trimming the deficit to 4-3. Fresno State then broke through in the eighth. After\nJett Ruby\nwas hit by a pitch and\nCam Schneider\nsingled, De La Maza came off the bench with an RBI single to tie the game. Payne followed two batters later with a two-run single to center, pushing the Bulldogs in front 6-4.\nUtah Tech responded immediately in the bottom of the eighth, capitalizing on an error and a wild pitch to score twice and knot the game at 6-6. After a scoreless ninth for both sides, Plasschaert opened the 10th-inning scoring with a solo shot to center to put Fresno State back on top. But in the bottom half, after a one-out walk, Finnegan Stewart hit a two-run homer to center to end it.\nNotes\nFresno State got scoreless relief outings from\nWyatt Thornbury\n,\nVictor Arreola\nand Douglas Crystal before the late Utah Tech push.\nNolen\u00a0and\u00a0Plasschaert\u00a0each homered, while Hewitt, Faust and Schneider were among the Bulldogs with multi-hit or timely-hit performances.\nThe Bulldogs finished with 12 hits, but three errors proved costly in the one-run defeat.\nUp next\nThe Bulldogs return home on Monday to face Long Beach State at 6 p.m. PT at Pete Beiden Field at Bob Bennett Stadium.",
